The paper deals with detecting pollution attacks in inter-session network coding, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and network security (cs.CR). The proposed detection schemes also involve network infrastructure (cs.NI) and data structures (cs.DS) for efficient detection. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of homomorphic MACs, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CC).
